cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of Raspberry Pi 2 SBCs as a cluster to compensate for their computing power. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on the hardware architecture of the Raspberry Pi 2 SBCs and their use as a mini supercomputer. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of a cluster for big data and computer simulation, which may involve networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the power consumption of the Raspberry Pi 2 SBCs and their performance as a cluster, which may involve system and control considerations. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is another possible category as the Raspberry Pi 2 SBCs are embedded systems and the paper discusses their use as a mini supercomputer.
